"Hello, World!"
This section is about writing the canonical "Hello, World!" program and its derivatives.
Now is a good time to get used to your development environment. Submit each program in
a separate source file named hsectioni.hsubsectioni.cpp.
2.1
Hello World I
Write a program that outputs "Hello, World!" by printing a const char * with value
"Hello, World!".
2.2
Hello World II
Write a program that outputs "Hello, World!" n times (where n is a nonnegative integer
that the user will input) with:
- a for loop.
- a while loop.
- a do...while loop.

More Programs
Now that you have had some practice working in your development environment, here are
some more challenging tasks. Again, submit your work (source code and answers to ques
tions) in an appropriately named text file.
3.1
Scope
For these questions, you are encouraged to use a computer.
